Description: Fragment of round handle of a Rhodian pottery pottery transport amphora, to sharp turn. Clay fine light orange-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Moschos. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0829.03.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0941)
